The evidence with the title 'Study: gun homicides, violence down sharply in past 20 years - CNN ' says May 9, 2013  ... " despite national attention to the issue of firearm violence, most Americans are unaware that gun crime is lower today than it was two decades ago , " the researchers say. A Pew survey of Americans in march found 56% believed gun- Related crime is higher than 20 years ago and only 12% said it's lower. 
